The paper deals with Zero-Shot Learning (ZSL) which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves projecting image data and semantic labels into a joint embedding space, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses semantic reconstruction and domain division constraints, which are related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) respectively.
